Diabetes Training Series



Date / Time
November 28, 2022 
10:00 am - 11:30 am



Categories

Health & Medicine




Sign up now for our three-week series on diabetes.
In this series, you will learn about diabetes, its impact on the body and the importance of keeping it under control. You will learn ways to help manage diabetes through healthy eating and will also participate in a live virtual cooking demo.
The recipe and cooking ingredients will be provided prior to the lesson.
Schedule:

Monday, Nov. 28, 10-11:30 a.m.: Instructor: Sheila Harmon, MSN, APRN, CDCES, PCMH-CCE Session 1 – ABC’s of Diabetes: A1C, Blood Pressure, Cholesterol.
Monday, Dec. 5, 10-11:30 a.m: Instructor: Sheila Harmon, MSN, APRN, CDCES, PCMH-CCE Session 2 – Healthy Eating and Nutrition
Monday, Dec. 19, 110-11:30 a.m: Instructor: Dorothy J. Collins, RD, LDN Session 3 – Healthy Cooking with Dorothy Collins Participants will view a live cooking demonstration.

Sessions will be presented virtually via Zoom.
Register online.
Event website.
Email uicchwconnect@gmail.com 
Phone 312-413-3996


